Installer python 3 via le web-installer, préciser "ajouter a PATH"
Installer les drivers daqmx
installer le package python via pip : $ python -m pip install nidaqmx

Go to the script folder of the python installation folder. For example, C:\Program Files (x86)\Python36-32\Scripts
Go to computer properties, then select Advanced system settings
In the Advanced tab click on Environment Variables.. 
Under system variable, select PATH and click on Edit
In Variable value, at the end, add a semicolon and path of script folder as above. For example, add ;C:\Program Files (x86)\Python36-32\Scripts
Also add address of the python folder to PATH of environment variable. For example, add at the end ;C:\Program Files (x86)\Python36-32

Je sais pas si c'est utile mais ca a marché du premier coup. Faire un test voltmètre

ref : https://knowledge.ni.com/KnowledgeArticleDetails?id=kA00Z0000019Pf1SAE&l=fr-FR
